<body>

    <h1>HTML Tag Examples and Explanations</h1>

    <div>
        <h2>Structural Tags</h2>
        <p>&lt;html&gt;: Represents the root of an HTML document.</p>
        <p>&lt;head&gt;: Contains meta-information about the HTML document.</p>
        <p>&lt;title&gt;: Sets the title of the HTML document.</p>
        <p>&lt;body&gt;: Contains the content of the HTML document.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Heading Tags</h2>
        <p>&lt;h1&gt; to &lt;h6&gt;: Define headings of different levels.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Paragraph Tags</h2>
        <p>&lt;p&gt;: Defines a paragraph.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Formatting Tags</h2>
        <p>&lt;strong&gt; or &lt;b&gt;: Represents strong importance or bold text.</p>
        <p>&lt;em&gt; or &lt;i&gt;: Represents emphasized text or italic text.</p>
        <p>&lt;u&gt;: Represents underlined text.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>List Tags</h2>
        <p>&lt;ul&gt;: Defines an unordered list.</p>
        <p>&lt;ol&gt;: Defines an ordered list.</p>
        <p>&lt;li&gt;: Defines a list item.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Anchor Tag</h2>
        <p>&lt;a&gt;: Defines a hyperlink for creating links to other pages or resources.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Image Tag</h2>
        <p>&lt;img&gt;: Embeds images into the document.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Table Tags</h2>
        <p>&lt;table&gt;: Defines a table.</p>
        <p>&lt;tr&gt;: Defines a table row.</p>
        <p>&lt;td&gt;: Defines a table cell (data cell).</p>
        <p>&lt;th&gt;: Defines a table header cell.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Form Tags</h2>
        <p>&lt;form&gt;: Defines an HTML form for user input.</p>
        <p>&lt;input&gt;: Defines an input field.</p>
        <p>&lt;button&gt;: Defines a clickable button.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Division Tag</h2>
        <p>&lt;div&gt;: Represents a division or section in an HTML document.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Span Tag</h2>
        <p>&lt;span&gt;: Used for applying styles to a specific part of text within a larger element.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2>Comment Tags</h2>
        <p>&lt;!-- Comment --&gt;: Used to add comments in the HTML code.</p>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
